description: The "synthetic.packages" table represents a collection of packages, each uniquely identified by the primary key "package_id," and associated with specific attributes such as "weight_kg," "length_cm," "width_cm," "height_cm," and a unique "tracking_number." While this table is not explicitly related to other tables via foreign keys, each package is likely part of a larger system for tracking shipments or deliveries, as suggested by its inclusion of "created_at" and "updated_at" timestamps. The table's role appears to be centralized around maintaining descriptive and logistical information about individual packages within the synthetic_250_postgres database.

columns.name: package_id
columns.description: This column uniquely identifies each package within the system. It automatically assigns consecutive numbers to new entries, serving as the primary key for package records.

columns.name: pack_id
columns.description: This column appears to represent unique identifiers assigned to packages, ensuring each package can be individually distinguished within the system. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: package_number
columns.description: Numerical identifier assigned to each package to ensure its unique distinction within the system. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: weight_kg
columns.description: This column represents the weight of individual packages in kilograms for a shipping or logistics context. The values range from around 14 to 96 kilograms, indicating varying sizes of packages.

columns.name: length_cm
columns.description: This column represents the physical length of packages measured in centimeters. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: width_cm
columns.description: This column represents the width dimension of packages measured in centimeters, as evidenced by the sample values. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: height_cm
columns.description: This column represents the height of packages measured in centimeters. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: tracking_number
columns.description: This column likely represents a unique identifier for packages in a logistics or delivery system, allowing for the tracking of individual packages through various stages of transit. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: This column records the date and time when a package entry is created. It reflects the moment the package was added to the system, with the ability to store unspecified timestamps.

columns.name: updated_at
columns.description: This column records the date and time when a package record was last modified. The values indicate historical timestamps reflecting updates made to package details.

indexes.index_definition: CREATE UNIQUE INDEX packages_pkey ON synthetic.packages USING btree (package_id)
